SJSFI FACULTY LEAVE POLICY TRAINING DOCUMENT

1. GENERAL LEAVE INQUIRIES

What types of leave are available for faculty?
Faculty members are eligible for various types of leave, including Sick Leave, Vacation Leave, Study Leave, Maternity/Paternity Leave, and Bereavement Leave. Specific policies apply to each type of leave.

Can I take a half-day leave?
Yes, half-day leaves are generally permitted for Sick Leave and Vacation Leave, subject to departmental approval and operational needs. Please specify if it's for the morning or afternoon when applying.

What's the maximum number of days I can take for vacation leave?
The maximum continuous vacation leave allowed is usually 15 days, but your total accrued vacation leave balance determines how many days you can take in a year. Please refer to the Vacation Leave Policy for full details.

Is there a specific time of year when I can't take leave?
Leave requests may be restricted during critical periods such as examination weeks, student registration, or major university events, unless it's an emergency or sick leave. Please check with your department head for specific blackout dates.

2. APPLYING FOR LEAVE

How do I apply for leave?
You can apply for leave directly through this chatbot by saying 'Apply for leave' or by navigating to the 'Leave Application' section in the dashboard. You'll need to specify the type of leave, dates, and reason.

What information do I need to provide when applying for sick leave?
For sick leave, you'll need to provide the start and end dates, and a brief reason. For leaves exceeding 3 days, a medical certificate may be required. The chatbot will guide you through the necessary fields.

Can I apply for leave for a future date?
Yes, you can apply for leave for any future date. It's recommended to submit vacation and study leave requests well in advance, typically at least 7 days prior to the start date, to allow for approval.

How do I cancel a submitted leave request?
To cancel a leave request, please go to the 'My Leave Requests' section on the dashboard and select the request you wish to cancel. If it's already approved, you might need to contact your department head or HR directly.

